        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>photographic paper [300014190], paper by function [300014146], paper (fiber product) [300014109], fiber by product [300014062], fiber and fiber by product [300014023], materials by physical form [300247256], materials by form [300014611], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Film or photographic paper that allows the image-bearing emulsion to be removed intact from the base material, usually for transfer to another, more substantial or transparent, support. The first major gelatin-emulsion stripping film was Eastman American film, offered in 1885.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Película o papel fotográfico que permite que la emulsión que contiene la imagen sea retirada intacta de su base material, habitualmente transfiriéndola a otro soporte, más sustancial o transparente. La primera película despegable de la emulsión gelatina fue la película Eastman American, en venta desde 1885.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Film of fotopapier waarmee de beelddragende emulsie in zijn geheel kan worden verwijderd van het basismateriaal, meestal om deze over te brengen op een andere, steviger of transparanter drager. Eastman American Film, die in 1885 op de markt kwam, was de eerste aftrekfilm met gelatine-emulsie van betekenis.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000119831/IATE: European Union Terminology (2022-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指可從基材上移除載像乳劑而不損害載像乳劑的底片或相紙，通常是為了轉移至另一個更堅固或更透明的基底。1885年，第一個重要的明膠乳劑剝膜底片—伊士曼美國底片—問世。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
